# HOWTO: Porting GDC to NetBSD 10 (amd64)

## Overview

Bootstrapping GDC on NetBSD requires multiple stages because GDC (GCC's D
compiler) generally needs a D compiler to build itself. GCC 10 is the last
version whose D frontend can be built with only a C++ compiler (no prior D
compiler needed), making it the ideal stage0.

Stages:
  stage0: GDC 10 (built from pkgsrc with C++ bootstrap, no D compiler needed)
  stage1: GDC 12 (built from pkgsrc using GDC 10 as D bootstrap compiler)
  final : GDC 15 (target)

## Prerequisites

- NetBSD 10 amd64
- pkgsrc tree at /usr/pkgsrc (comes with NetBSD)
- pkgsrc bootstrapped (pkg_install, digest, etc.)
- At least 8 GiB of available disk space, I believe
- 4 GiB recommended, 6 GiB for final stage
- Obviously, the more cores you throw at it, the faster it will compile
- Tested with pkgsrc-2025Q4

## Notes

- If the process gets OOM'd, run 'make clean' and restart your build.
  You will have to redo your symlinks.

## Stage 0: Building GDC 10 from pkgsrc

GCC 10 is the last version whose D frontend includes a C++ fallback for
bootstrapping. NetBSD pkgsrc has the `gcc-d` option for lang/gcc10.

### 1. Enable the D language option

Add to /etc/mk.conf:

    PKG_OPTIONS.gcc10+= gcc-d

Other useful settings:

    MAKE_JOBS= 8          # parallel build (adjust to core count)

In /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc10/options.mk:

    PKG_SUPPORTED_OPTIONS= ... gcc-d
    
    .if !empty(PKG_OPTIONS:Mgcc-d)
    LANGS+=			d
    .endif

### 2. Build and install

    cd /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc10
    make                  # as root, or with appropriate privileges
    make install          # as root

This installs GDC 10 to /usr/pkg/gcc10/bin/gdc.

If digests fail (after modifying options), clean your work and retry:

    make distclean && make checksum

### 3. Verify

    /usr/pkg/gcc10/bin/gdc --version
    # gdc (GCC) 10.5.0 - D frontend version 2.076

Test with a simple program:

    cat > /tmp/hello.d << 'EOF'
    import std.stdio;
    void main() { writeln("Hello!"); }
    EOF
    /usr/pkg/gcc10/bin/gdc /tmp/hello.d -o /tmp/hello && /tmp/hello

Note: You may see linker warnings about compatibility references to
nanosleep/clock_gettime/time. These are caused by NetBSD's ABI renames
(see "libphobos patches" in the final stage section). They do not affect
functionality but can be fixed with equivalent pragma(mangle) patches.

To reclaim some space, feel free to invoke 'make clean' in
/usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc10.

### Known issues (stage0)

- The linker warnings about compatibility time functions are cosmetic.
- gcc10-libs must be installed alongside gcc10 (pkgsrc handles this
  automatically as a dependency).

## Stage 1: Building GDC 12 from pkgsrc

GCC 12 (D frontend 2.100) serves as the intermediate step between GDC 10
and GDC 15. The pkgsrc gcc12 package supports the `gcc-d` option and uses
gcc10 as the D bootstrap compiler.

### 1. Enable the D language option

Add to /etc/mk.conf (if not already present):

    PKG_OPTIONS.gcc12+= gcc-d

GCC 12 already includes the gcc-d block with gcc10 as bootstrap, so there is no
need to modify options.mk at all.

### 2. Pre-build fixes

Apply these fixes before running `make`:

a) Fix LLVM libunwind header conflict

If the LLVM `libunwind` package is installed, its `/usr/pkg/include/unwind.h`
shadows GCC's own `unwind.h`, causing build failures in libgcc with errors
about undefined `_Unwind_Ptr`, `_Unwind_Word`, etc.

Temporarily move the conflicting headers:

    mv /usr/pkg/include/unwind.h /usr/pkg/include/unwind.h.bak
    mv /usr/pkg/include/__libunwind_config.h /usr/pkg/include/__libunwind_config.h.bak
    mv /usr/pkg/include/libunwind.h /usr/pkg/include/libunwind.h.bak

b) Fix static linking of libgcc_eh

The gcc12 Makefile's BOOT_LDFLAGS uses `-static-libstdc++ -static-libgcc`
but doesn't link `libgcc_eh`, causing undefined `_Unwind_*` symbol errors
during the stage1 link. Edit `/usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc12/Makefile`:

    # Change this line:
    BOOT_LDFLAGS=       -static-libstdc++ -static-libgcc ${LDFLAGS_FOR_TARGET}
    # To:
    BOOT_LDFLAGS=       -static-libstdc++ -static-libgcc -lgcc_eh ${LDFLAGS_FOR_TARGET}

### 3. Run make (first pass — will fail, this is expected)

    cd /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc12
    make                  # as root; let it run until it fails

The build will fail at configure with a message like "GDC is required to
build d". This is expected — pkgsrc created a `gdc` wrapper symlink but
pointed it at gcc6 (the build compiler) instead of gcc10.

### 4. Fix the GDC wrapper symlink (pkgsrc bug)

    ls -la /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc12/work/.gcc/bin/gdc
    # It will point to /usr/pkg/gcc6/bin/gdc (wrong). Fix it:
    rm /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc12/work/.gcc/bin/gdc
    # It may not even exist, that's okay, but this is important:
    ln -s /usr/pkg/gcc10/bin/gdc /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc12/work/.gcc/bin/gdc

If the symlink does not exist at all, `make` hasn't reached the
wrapper-creation phase yet. Re-run `make` — it will create the symlink
and then fail at configure, at which point you can apply the fix.

### 5. Build and install (second pass)

    cd /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc12
    make                  # as root; resumes from where it failed
    make install          # as root

Restore the libunwind headers after install:

    mv /usr/pkg/include/unwind.h.bak /usr/pkg/include/unwind.h
    mv /usr/pkg/include/__libunwind_config.h.bak /usr/pkg/include/__libunwind_config.h
    mv /usr/pkg/include/libunwind.h.bak /usr/pkg/include/libunwind.h

Note: gcc6 will be built as a transitive dependency (from gcc10's
buildlink3.mk). This adds significant build time but is automatic.

This installs GDC 12 to /usr/pkg/gcc12/bin/gdc.

### 6. Verify

    /usr/pkg/gcc12/bin/gdc --version
    # gdc (GCC) 12.5.0

Test with a simple program:

    /usr/pkg/gcc12/bin/gdc /tmp/hello.d -o /tmp/hello12 && /tmp/hello12

### Known issues (stage1)

- The same linker warnings about compatibility time functions appear as
  with stage0 (see "libphobos patches" in the final stage section).
- DWARF debug section warnings ("can't find .debug_ranges section") are
  cosmetic and do not affect functionality.
- The gcc6 transitive build dependency may fail to fetch isl-0.14.tar.bz2
  from some mirrors; pkgsrc will retry alternate mirrors automatically.

## Final Stage: Building GDC 15 from pkgsrc

GCC 15 (GDC with D frontend 2.109+) is the target. The pkgsrc gcc15 package
does NOT include a `gcc-d` option by default — it must be added manually.

### 1. Add gcc-d option to the gcc15 pkgsrc package

Edit `/usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc15/options.mk`:

a) Add `gcc-d` to `PKG_SUPPORTED_OPTIONS`.

b) Append the D language block at the end of options.mk:

    # GDC is required to build d, use GDC 12 as bootstrap compiler
    .if !empty(PKG_OPTIONS:Mgcc-d)
    LANGS+=		d
    GCC_REQD=		12
    _GCC_VARS+=		GDC
    _GCC_GDC=		${_GCC_DIR}/bin/${_GCC_BIN_PREFIX}gdc${GCC_VERSION_SUFFIX}
    _ALIASES.GDC=		gdc
    .include "../../lang/gcc12/buildlink3.mk"
    post-tools: ${_GCC_GDC}
    .if !target(${_GCC_GDC})
    ${_GCC_GDC}:
    	${RUN}${MKDIR} ${.TARGET:H}
    .    if !empty(COMPILER_USE_SYMLINKS:M[Yy][Ee][Ss])
    	${RUN}${RM} -f ${.TARGET}
    	${RUN}${LN} -s ${_GCCBINDIR}/${.TARGET:T} ${.TARGET}
    .    else
    	${RUN}                                  \
    	(${ECHO} '#!${TOOLS_SHELL}';            \
    	 ${ECHO} 'exec ${_GCCBINDIR}/${.TARGET:T} "$$@"'; \
    	) > ${.TARGET}
    	${RUN}${CHMOD} +x ${.TARGET}
    .    endif
    .    for _alias_ in ${_ALIASES.${_var}}
    	${RUN}                                  \
    	if [ ! -x "${.TARGET:H}/${_alias_}" ]; then \
    		${LN} -f -s ${.TARGET:T} ${.TARGET:H}/${_alias_}; \
    	fi
    .    endfor
    .endif
    .endif

### 2. Enable the D language option

Add to /etc/mk.conf:

    PKG_OPTIONS.gcc15+= gcc-d

### 3. Compile pkgtools/cwrappers

GCC 15 requires cwrappers.

# cd /usr/pkgsrc/pkgtools/cwrappers
# make && make install
===> Installing binary package of cwrapper-20220403

Done. I believe only "make install" is enough.

Should be ready to make GCC 15.

### 4. Fix the GDC wrapper symlink (same pkgsrc bug as stage1)

Same issue as stage1: the symlink only appears after `make` runs far
enough to create wrappers, then fails at configure. Let `make` fail
first, then fix the symlink:

    ls -la /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc15/work/.gcc/bin/gdc
    # It will point to /usr/pkg/gcc6/bin/gdc (wrong). Fix it:
    rm /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc15/work/.gcc/bin/gdc
    ln -s /usr/pkg/gcc12/bin/gdc /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc15/work/.gcc/bin/gdc

Then re-run `make` to continue.

### 5. Fix LLVM libunwind header conflict (same as stage1)

    mv /usr/pkg/include/unwind.h /usr/pkg/include/unwind.h.bak
    mv /usr/pkg/include/__libunwind_config.h /usr/pkg/include/__libunwind_config.h.bak
    mv /usr/pkg/include/libunwind.h /usr/pkg/include/libunwind.h.bak

Restore after the build completes.

### 6. Fix static linking of libgcc_eh (same as stage1)

Edit `/usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc15/Makefile`:

    # Change:
    BOOT_LDFLAGS=       -static-libstdc++ -static-libgcc ${LDFLAGS_FOR_TARGET}
    # To:
    BOOT_LDFLAGS=       -static-libstdc++ -static-libgcc -lgcc_eh ${LDFLAGS_FOR_TARGET}

### 7. Build and install

    cd /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc15
    make                  # as root; will fail at configure, fix symlink, re-run
    make install          # as root

Don't forget to restore the libunwind headers after install:

    mv /usr/pkg/include/unwind.h.bak /usr/pkg/include/unwind.h
    mv /usr/pkg/include/__libunwind_config.h.bak /usr/pkg/include/__libunwind_config.h
    mv /usr/pkg/include/libunwind.h.bak /usr/pkg/include/libunwind.h

### 8. Verify

    /usr/pkg/gcc15/bin/gdc --version
    # gdc (GCC) 15.2.0

    /usr/pkg/gcc15/bin/gdc /tmp/hello.d -o /tmp/hello15 && /tmp/hello15
    # Hello from GDC on NetBSD!

### 9. Apply libphobos patches for NetBSD symbol renaming

GDC 15 compiles and links correctly, but without patches, the linker emits
warnings about compatibility symbols (nanosleep, clock_gettime, etc.).
This is because NetBSD renamed many POSIX functions during its 64-bit
time_t and statvfs ABI transitions (e.g. nanosleep -> __nanosleep50,
statvfs -> __statvfs90). D's extern(C) bindings bypass C headers and
resolve to the old compat stubs.

The fix adds `pragma(mangle, "...")` annotations to the NetBSD sections
of libphobos/libdruntime, using the same technique already used for Musl
in these files.

Copy the following patches into /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc15/patches/:

    patches/gcc15/patch-libphobos_libdruntime_core_sys_posix_time.d
    patches/gcc15/patch-libphobos_libdruntime_core_sys_posix_sys_time.d
    patches/gcc15/patch-libphobos_libdruntime_core_sys_posix_sys_statvfs.d
    patches/gcc15/patch-libphobos_libdruntime_core_sys_posix_stdc_time.d
    patches/gcc15/patch-libphobos_libdruntime_core_sys_posix_sys_select.d

Then update the distinfo checksums:

    cd /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc15
    make makepatchsum

Symbols fixed across these patches:
  time.d:       clock_getres, clock_gettime, clock_settime, nanosleep,
                timer_gettime, timer_settime, timegm, ctime_r, gmtime_r,
                localtime_r
  sys/time.d:   getitimer, gettimeofday, setitimer, utimes
  statvfs.d:    statvfs, fstatvfs
  stdc/time.d:  tzset
  select.d:     pselect, select

If you have already built gcc15 without these patches, you can rebuild
just libphobos without a full GCC rebuild:

    cd /usr/pkgsrc/lang/gcc15/work/build/x86_64--netbsd/libphobos
    gmake -j8 clean
    gmake -j8
    gmake install            # as root

### Known issues (final stage)

- Without the libphobos patches above, there are cosmetic linker warnings
  about compatibility time functions; the patches eliminate them.
- DWARF warnings ("can't find .debug_ranges section") are cosmetic and due
  to DWARF5 and old binutils version. Use -gdwarf-4 to suppress.
  This is not required with the final stage with libphobos patches, because
  the compat module is no longer targeted.
- The gcc-d option does not exist in the stock pkgsrc gcc15 package and
  must be added manually (step 1 above).
- The GDC wrapper symlink bug persists from gcc12 — always check and fix
  after the initial `make` run.
- When using pkgin upgrade, it will overwrite our gcc binaries.
  If you do update them, you will have to rebuild them.

## Notes for AArch64 porting

- The same pkgsrc approach should work on NetBSD/aarch64.
- Architecture-specific configure flags will differ (no --with-arch=nocona,
  --with-tune=nocona, --with-fpmath=sse).
- AArch64 may need different patches for D runtime/phobos (thread/fiber
  support, signal handling).
- Verify that libphobos has proper AArch64 support in the target GCC version.
